  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ddb\">\n<p>Drawing on the deepest fears of a group of creatures, you create illusory creatures in their minds, visible only to them. Each creature in a 30-foot-radius &amp;Reference[sphere]{sphere} centered on a point of your choice within range must make a &amp;Reference[wis]{Wisdom} saving throw. On a failed save, a creature becomes &amp;Reference[frightened]{frightened} for the duration. The &amp;Reference[ill]{illusion} calls on the creature's deepest fears, manifesting its worst nightmares as an implacable threat. At the end of each of the &amp;Reference[frightened]{frightened} creature's turns, it must succeed on a &amp;Reference[wis]{Wisdom} saving throw or take 4d10 &amp;Reference[psychic]{psychic} damage. On a successful save, the spell ends for that creature.</p>\n</div>",
